Token.Abstract: Returns a Boolean indicating whether the app is currently registered for remote notifications.

ReturnValue.Abstract: BOOL YES if the app is registered for remote notifications and received its device token or NO if registration has not occurred, has failed, or has been denied by the user.

Parameter.Name: launchOptions
Parameter.Abstract: A dictionary indicating the reason the app was launched (if any). The contents of this dictionary may be empty in situations where the user launched the app directly. For information about the possible keys in this dictionary and how to handle them.

Parameter.Name: deviceToken
Parameter.Abstract: A token that identifies the device to APNs.

Parameter.Name: userInfo
Parameter.Abstract: A dictionary that contains information related to the remote notification, potentially including a badge number for the app icon, an alert sound, an alert message to display to the user, a notification identifier, and custom data. The provider originates it as a JSON-defined dictionary that iOS converts to an NSDictionary object; the dictionary may contain only property-list objects plus NSNull.

Parameter.Name: handler
Parameter.Abstract: The block to execute when the download operation is complete. When calling this block, pass in the fetch result value that best describes the results of your download operation. You must call this handler and should do so as soon as possible. For a list of possible values, see the UIBackgroundFetchResult type.

Parameter.Name: handleDeepLink
Parameter.Abstract: Whether or not notification manager should attempt to open the remote notification deeplink, if present
